properties.name: Netitishi
properties.comments:
Buried in 4’ of ice and snow, believe it or not had trouble even locating the antennas under the ice.  Took 2.5 hours just to dig it out.
The main problem came when setting up the gnome.  Although we still had lots of gear we were short a non-USB gps to hook up to the Pi. Long story short, after a long visit there we left the RPi on there without a GPS.  Obviously not ideal, but we should still be able to pull detections off of it and manually adjust the date as it still creates a file per day starting at Jan 1, 2000, which will really be May 24, 2019.  May add a gps in July if possible to access.

November 2019 notes: tower had collapsed at some point before mid-July.
